* SIP\n(RFC 3261)
** Purpose
*** Signaling, not media
*** Locate, negotiate, manage
*** Five facets\n(location, availability,\ncapabilities, setup, management)
*** Works with RTP / SDP / RTSP
** Elements
*** UA (UAC / UAS)
*** Proxy (stateful / stateless)
*** Redirect server
*** Registrar
*** B2BUA
*** Location service
** Layered model
*** Syntax & encoding (ABNF)
*** Transport (UDP/TCP/TLS/SCTP)
*** Transaction
*** Transaction user (core)
** Messages
*** Methods\n(INVITE ACK BYE\nCANCEL REGISTER OPTIONS)
*** Responses 1xx-6xx
*** Headers\n(Via To From Call-ID\nCSeq Contact Max-Forwards)
** Abstractions
*** Transaction\n(INVITE vs non-INVITE)
*** Dialog\n(Call-ID + 2 tags)
*** Registration & AOR
** Security
*** Threats\n(hijacking, impersonation,\ntampering, teardown, DoS)
*** TLS / IPsec
*** SIPS URI
*** HTTP Digest
*** S/MIME
@endmindmap
